  "body": "Operating system: Arch\r\n```console\r\n$ lsb_release -a\r\nLSB Version:\t1.4\r\nDistributor ID:\tArch\r\nDescription:\tArch Linux\r\nRelease:\trolling\r\nCodename:\tn/a\r\n```\r\n\r\nRunning `beacon-chain` image in docker, latest image.\r\n```\r\n$ docker images | grep beacon-chain\r\ngcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain       latest              b96edb5366e6        50 years ago        60.1MB\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt seems to be related to this issue.\r\nhttps://github.com/golang/go/issues/37436\r\n\r\nWhich is a problem with the current go version.\r\n\r\nThe node keeps crashing and I am unable to validate any more.\r\n\r\n```console\r\n[2020-03-23 10:09:39]  INFO blockchain: Executing state transition on block root=0xe7ddd6f6... slot=528648\r\nruntime: mlock of signal stack failed: 12\r\nruntime: increase the mlock limit (ulimit -l) or\r\nruntime: update your kernel to 5.3.15+, 5.4.2+, or 5.5+\r\nfatal error: mlock failed\r\n\r\nruntime stack:\r\nruntime.throw(0x16db647, 0xc)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/panic.go:1112 +0x72\r\nruntime.mlockGsignal(0xc014e1d080)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/os_linux_x86.go:72 +0x107\r\nruntime.mpreinit(0xc005824e00)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/os_linux.go:341 +0x78\r\nruntime.mcommoninit(0xc005824e00)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:630 +0x108\r\nruntime.allocm(0xc00004a800, 0x0, 0x1)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:1390 +0x14e\r\nruntime.newm(0x0, 0xc00004a800)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:1704 +0x39\r\nruntime.startm(0xc00004a800, 0x26df600)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:1869 +0x12a\r\nruntime.handoffp(0xc00004a800)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:1896 +0x52\r\nruntime.retake(0x3ef51753be8d, 0xc00004a800)\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:4628 +0x157\r\nruntime.sysmon()\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:4537 +0x138\r\nruntime.mstart1()\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:1097 +0xc3\r\nruntime.mstart()\r\n        GOROOT/src/runtime/proc.go:1062 +0x6e\r\n\r\ngoroutine 1 [chan 